{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0175tPAFMh6L7XcdnL45f6Tk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Ralph Fix Plan\n2\t\n3\t## High Priority\n4\t\n5\t- [ ] Set up test infrastructure: install Vitest (or Jest), configure a test database connection using `DATABASE_URL` from `.env`, add a test script to `package.json`\n6\t- [ ] Tests — `signUp` Server Action: creates a User with a bcrypt-hashed password; returns error for duplicate email; returns error for missing fields\n7\t- [ ] Tests — `login` Server Action: succeeds with correct credentials; returns error for wrong password; returns error for unregistered email\n8\t- [ ] Tests — `createPost` Server Action: persists a Post attributed to the authenticated User; returns error for empty content; returns error when called without a session\n9\t\n10\t## Medium Priority\n11\t\n12\t- [ ] Tests — Feed page: all Posts returned newest-first; empty state when no Posts exist\n13\t- [ ] Tests — Profile page: only the specified User's Posts are returned newest-first; 404 for unknown User id; empty state when User has no Posts; Post from User A does not appear on User B's Profile\n14\t\n15\t## Low Priority\n16\t\n17\t- [ ] Verify Vercel deployment: app accessible at public URL, sign up / log in / create Post work in production\n18\t\n19\t## Completed\n20\t\n21\t- [x] Scaffold Next.js app with Tailwind + shadcn/ui\n22\t- [x] Set up Prisma with PostgreSQL schema (User, Post)\n23\t- [x] Configure NextAuth.js v5 with credentials provider\n24\t- [x] Build sign up and log in pages\n25\t- [x] Build post creation Server Action\n26\t- [x] Build Feed page\n27\t- [x] Build Profile pages\n28\t- [x] Build Navbar with auth state\n29\t- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n30\t\n31\t## Notes\n32\t\n33\t- Use a real test database, never mocks — divergence between mocked and real DB has caused bugs before\n34\t- The Prisma client requires the PrismaPg adapter (Prisma 7) — follow `src/lib/prisma.ts` exactly\n35\t- Next.js 16 uses `src/proxy.ts` not `src/middleware.ts`\n36\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39221e05-7a5e-418e-a005-1804020ffd62","uuid":"8688e612-e48f-4278-93cd-f90474461d88","timestamp":"2026-05-26T21:09:01.373Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/enpitech/fb2-b/.ralph/fix_plan.md","content":"# Ralph Fix Plan\n\n## High Priority\n\n- [ ] Set up test infrastructure: install Vitest (or Jest), configure a test database connection using `DATABASE_URL` from `.env`, add a test script to `package.json`\n- [ ] Tests — `signUp` Server Action: creates a User with a bcrypt-hashed password; returns error for duplicate email; returns error for missing fields\n- [ ] Tests — `login` Server Action: succeeds with correct credentials; returns error for wrong password; returns error for unregistered email\n- [ ] Tests — `createPost` Server Action: persists a Post attributed to the authenticated User; returns error for empty content; returns error when called without a session\n\n## Medium Priority\n\n- [ ] Tests — Feed page: all Posts returned newest-first; empty state when no Posts exist\n- [ ] Tests — Profile page: only the specified User's Posts are returned newest-first; 404 for unknown User id; empty state when User has no Posts; Post from User A does not appear on User B's Profile\n\n## Low Priority\n\n- [ ] Verify Vercel deployment: app accessible at public URL, sign up / log in / create Post work in production\n\n## Completed\n\n- [x] Scaffold Next.js app with Tailwind + shadcn/ui\n- [x] Set up Prisma with PostgreSQL schema (User, Post)\n- [x] Configure NextAuth.js v5 with credentials provider\n- [x] Build sign up and log in pages\n- [x] Build post creation Server Action\n- [x] Build Feed page\n- [x] Build Profile pages\n- [x] Build Navbar with auth state\n- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n\n## Notes\n\n- Use a real test database, never mocks — divergence between mocked and real DB has caused bugs before\n- The Prisma client requires the PrismaPg adapter (Prisma 7) — follow `src/lib/prisma.ts` exactly\n- Next.js 16 uses `src/proxy.ts` not `src/middleware.ts`\n","numLines":36,"startLine":1,"totalLines":36}}}
