{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BNsq4N7UskvB3Zkg4u3Rk6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll set up Vitest with the necessary configuration. I need to:\n1. Install vitest and related packages\n2. Create vitest config\n3. Add test script to package.json\n4. Create a test helper for DB connection\n\nThe actions use `\"use server\"` and Next.js-specific things like `auth()`, `revalidatePath`, `redirect`. Testing these directly is tricky. The fix_plan says \"real test database, never mocks\".\n\nLet me install vitest and set up the infrastructure first, then write the tests.\n\nFor the signUp tests, I'll need to test the logic without the NextAuth `signIn` call. \n\nThe tricky part is that the Server Actions mix database operations with Next.js-specific functions. I think the best approach is to mock the Next.js parts like `auth`, `signIn`, `redirect`, and `revalidatePath` while keeping the database interactions real—that way I'm testing the actual logic against a real database without getting tangled up in Next.js internals.\n\nI'll set up vitest with a config file, create a test database helper, and write tests for the signUp action. I need to install vitest, the coverage plugin, and dotenv to handle environment variables.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":24688,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39221e05-7a5e-418e-a005-1804020ffd62","uuid":"6f7a4eb1-37c6-416f-8633-ad9f1dfea832","request_id":"req_011CbRs8D4tHmjh6wWgNMdkd"}
